headline: Invesco (IVZ): Evaluating Valuation as SEC Delays Solana ETF Decision on Regulatory Uncertainty
summary: Invesco (IVZ) has found itself in the spotlight after the SEC postponed decisions on exchange-traded funds tied to solana. The partial U.S. government shutdown paused reviews and left Invesco’s ETF ambitions temporarily on hold. See our latest analysis for Invesco. Invesco’s shares have shown strong momentum lately, with a 3.65% jump in the latest session and a 39.13% share price return over the past 90 days.
